Feature: AI Agent Paradigm for Regenerative Communities

  As a community building on the AI agent paradigm
  I want systems that take high-level goals and execute complex multi-step plans
  So that autonomous action delivers measurable production value

  Background:
    Given 18 of 30 trending GitHub projects are agent-related in May 2026
    And GitHub reached 4.3 million AI repositories in 2025 (178% increase from 2024)
    And MCP has become essential infrastructure, donated to Linux Foundation Agentic AI Foundation
    And terminal has re-emerged as the primary AI battleground

  Scenario: Terminal-based agents lead the market
    Given Rust-based tools (DeepSeek-TUI, jcode, Warp) lead the terminal battleground
    When agents operate through terminal interfaces
    Then low-latency, high-throughput interaction occurs
    And the community adopts terminal-native agent patterns

  Scenario: Agent skills encode institutional knowledge
    Given SKILL.md files encode practices for AI coding assistants
    When a new agent joins the community
    Then it reads relevant SKILL.md files
    And executes with community-aligned behavior from first interaction
    And institutional knowledge remains portable across agent implementations

  Scenario: MCP standardizes tool integration
    Given Model Context Protocol connects agents to external tools
    When a community agent needs to access external services
    Then MCP provides standardized connection without custom integration
    And tool availability expands without agent code changes
    And the protocol enables agent interoperability across the community

  Scenario: Tight feedback loops enable proof-of-regeneration
    Given financial AI agents (TradingAgents, dexter) represent the leading vertical
    When autonomous AI agents deliver production value
    Then measurable feedback enables continuous improvement
    And proof-of-regeneration creates real-world ecological verification before rewards unlock
    And the same feedback pattern applies to regenerative community metrics

  Scenario: Compiled corpora replace manual indexing
    Given Karpathy's LLM wiki pattern applies to community knowledge
    When the system builds a persistent wiki from documents
    Then graph relevance and vector search operate together
    And Louvain community detection identifies knowledge clusters
    And Deep Research navigates the corpus without manual structure

  Scenario: AI agents are as foundational to 2030s as microservices to 2010s
    Given the infrastructure layer is being built now (MCP, agent skills, terminal agents, orchestration)
    When the community builds on top of this layer
    Then regenerative systems leverage the dominant software paradigm of the era
    And the community avoids building alongside the paradigm rather than on top of it

  Scenario: Autonomous execution delivers measurable value
    Given task decomposition, tool selection, context management, and outcome verification are automated
    When a community member sets a high-level goal
    Then the full loop from goal to result executes with minimal human intervention
    And measurable outcomes are verified automatically
    And the agent paradigm solves the fundamental coordination problem previous architectures could not
